   INSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS

   1. Unix
   -------

Compilers:
 - G++
 - clang

Dependencies:
 - Boost::Context (optional)
 - Valgrind development files (optional)
 
Coroutine systems available:
 - ucontext
 - Boost::Context (fcontext)
 - POSIX threads

The following commands configure, compile and install libieee1666:
$ ./configure --prefix=<install directory>
$ make
$ make install

   1.1 Debian package creation
   ---------------------------

The following command create the debian source package:
$ make deb-source

The following command create the debian binary packages:
$ make deb-binary
   
   1.2 RPM package creation
   ------------------------

The following command create the RPM source package:
$ make rpm-source

The following command create the RPM binary packages:
$ make rpm-binary

   2. Windows
   ----------

Compilers:
 - mingw32 (32 bits)
 - mingw-w64 (32 and 64 bits)
 
Coroutine systems available:
 - Windows Fiber
 - Boost::Context (fcontext)
 - POSIX threads

The following commands configure, compile and install libieee1666:
$ ./configure --prefix=<install directory>
$ make
$ make install
